El archivo debe ser un csv con al menos cuatro columnas con los valores: FECHABP, DESVIACION, IDFECHA y YACIMIENTO

Definicin de la Funcin SPD

SPD<-function(ages,ageSds,calCurve="intcal13",ids=NULL, plot_SPD=F, breaks=NULL){
    
    bp<-BchronCalibrate(ages=ages,ageSds=ageSds,calCurves=rep(calCurve,length(ages)),ids=ids)
    
    densities<-c()
    years<-c()
    
    for(i in 1:length(ages)){
        densities<-c(densities,bp[[i]]$densities)
        years<-c(years,bp[[i]]$ageGrid)
    }
    
    # Complete date range - this should add 0 values to the empty bins.
    if (is.null(breaks)) breaks<-seq(min(years),max(years)) # if breaks are not specified, use 1-yr bins
    b<-rep(0,length(breaks))
    years<-c(years,breaks)
    densities<-c(densities,b)
    
    densities<-densities/sum(densities) #sums to unity
    
    densities <- densities [years %in% min(breaks):max(breaks)]
    years     <- years     [years %in% min(breaks):max(breaks)]
    
    #SPD<-aggregate(densities~years,FUN=sum) ; colnames(SPD)<-c("bin","density")
    SPD<-aggregate(densities~cut(years,breaks,include.lowest = TRUE, labels = breaks[-1]),FUN=sum)
    colnames(SPD)<-c("bin","density")
    SPD$breaks<-breaks[-1]
    
    #plotting
    if(plot_SPD==T){
        plot(SPD$density~SPD$breaks,xlim=c(6000,4600),ylim=range(SPD$density),xlab="calendar year BP",ylab="density",type="h",col= "dark red") #Aqu hay que poner el intervalo temporal que se quiera presentar 
        #abline(v=seq(6000,4600,by=-50),col=("light blue"))#Aqu hay que poner el intervalo temporal que se quiera presentar 
        abline(v=seq(6000,4600,by=-100),col=("dark grey"))#Aqu hay que poner el intervalo temporal que se quiera presentar 
    }
    
    list(density=SPD$density,breaks=SPD$breaks)
}

Llamada a la funcin SPD con plot_SPD a true para que imprima el resultado

SPD<-SPD(ages,ageSds,calCurve="intcal13",ids=idfecha, plot_SPD=TRUE, breaks = NULL)
